inn1.comm: full and a touch of outswing and Watson moves forward and drives through extra cover on one knee for four
angled into leg stump and Watson clips it off his pads, fine of Bond for four
better length this time from Southee and Watson defends off the outside half of the blade to point
back of a length and Watson guides it past second slip to third man and they run well for two
angled into the pads and and he whips it behind square and he times it far better than first expected as it rolls away across the quick outfield for four
half volley with no swing this time and driven back down the ground to mid off. Great start for Australia
great start from Bond as he hits a good length and Haddin lifts his hands high over the top of the bounce of the ball and through to the keeper
identical delivery and result as Haddin shoulders arms outside the line of off stump
and again from Bond as he finds a consistent channel with Haddin allowing it through to the keeper
Bond finds a good channel again and Haddin, knowing how good the track is, is content on having a look at the first over, allowing it through to McCullum
fuller and a hint of inswing from Bond has Haddin driving off the inside edge through backward square for three where Southee and Ingram combine to save the boundary on the rope
Bond hits the channel again and Watson is happy to let it through to McCullum
more energy from Southee this time as he hits a great length and it flies through to McCullum at chest height
fuller on middle stump and driven to mid on
good length but a fraction wider and Haddin plays the cut but misses
full delivery and Haddin drives on the up to Oram at mid off
good length but too much width and Haddin drives gloriously through cover point for four. Such good hands and great timing from the wicketkeeper
back of a length from Southee forces Haddin to play tighter this time and he defends to point
145 kph, just short of yorker length from Bond and Watson digs it out to cover
too full from Bond and Watson goes down on one knee and drives gorgeously for four through extra cover. Superb stroke
short and wide and it gets the treatment as Watson cuts powerfully backward of point for four
better channel from Bond and Watson guides it to third man
short and at the body and Haddin plays neatly into the leg side
better length and Haddin uses the pace to guide it fine but hits it to backward point
good length and Watson drives on the up but is hurried a little, it takes the stickers high on the bat and goes safely in the air through mid off but it's not hit well enough to get four
full and driven back past Southee's head, where he just gets out of the way, and Oram dives at mid off to keep the scoring to one
angled into leg stump and Watson pushes into the leg side
decent length but the line which attacks off stump has Watson defending into the off side
decent length but just too straight and Watson pulls awkwardly to deep square leg
decent length from Southee but without any swing, Haddin just hits perfectly through the line for four. So easy on the eye is Haddin
slower ball from Bond and Watson defends back to the bowler
short from Bond but not  bouncer and Watson leans back and clubs it over mid wicket for six. That is a pure pull shot
low full toss and Watson maintains his shape perfectly, plays it late under the eyes and drives straight back past the bowler for four. Impeccable timing
slower ball on a good length and  Watson defends into the off side
Bond loses his line and angles into leg and he works it to mid wicket
superb delivery from Bond as he angles it towards the batsman from wide on the crease then it straightens, Haddin looks to play through mid on and the ball takes out off stump
good length from Oram forces Watson into a defensive push into the off side
Oram's line is immediately straighter and Watson pushes to mid wicket
back of a length just on or outside off stump and Watson defends with soft hands to McCullum who moves quickly to his right to prevent the single
Oram settling in on a good channel and Watson defends with soft hands into the off side
Oram strays this time and Watson clips it fine but straight to Bond at short fine leg
slower ball and Watson leans into it and hits it high into the leg side. It bounces just in fron tof the rope for four
144 kph, good start to Ponting as Bond hits a good length on off stump and Ponting defends into the off side
good bouncer from Bond and it hurries Ponting up as he gets inside the line without playing a shot
Bond attacks the stumps this time and Ponting pushes into the leg side to get underway
good length but driven hard into the pitch and over Bond's outstretched hand and straight down the ground for a couple
back of a length but wider of off and Watson guides to third man
Bond really bends his back, hits a good length and Ponting is back and defending into the off side
good length and Watson drives back to the bowler
back of a length but wider this time and Watson guides it straight to short third man

Oram gets the breakthrough. He really hist the deck with this one and it bounces a little more than Watson expects and it takes him high on the bat as he pulls high into the leg side wehre Ingram comes in from the boundery and takes a good catch low down
back of a length and defended into the off side
good channel again from Oram and Ponting is back and leaving
slower ball and it's a half volley which Plonting pumps back down the ground through mid on for four
Bond continues to bend his back and Clarke pushes into the off side
good length but wider of off stump and Clarke is happy to let it go through to the keeper
back of a length but wider this time and Clarke drives of the back foot to point
good length again and at the body and Clarke defends into the off side
good bumper from Bond and Clarke ducks awkwardly underneath, the ball just missing his helmet
fuller and straighter this time and Clarke plays to mid wicket
good length and Ponting comes forward, the bounce surprises him and it takes the shoulder of the bat and flies to Broom at backward point
good length and Ponting waits for the ball this time and guides to Broom at backward point
identical delivery and result as this time Broom does even better, diving further, to save the single
back of a length and eased behind point, using the pace, and they take two to third man
fuller this time and Ponting sees it early and tries to hit over mid off but it takes the edge and loops over backward point to Tuffey at third man
fuller and driven neatly to mid on
short and wide but cut straight to point
back of a length and Ponting drives but gets it high on the bat and Guptill moves in quickly to save one
good channel from Tuffey and Ponting tries to force it through the off side but gets a bottom edge into the ground
good length and driven off the back foot to point
fuller in length and Ponting drives but closes the face at the last second and works it throguh forward square leg for three
good length but the line of middle stump allows Clarke to push towards mid on and get a sharp single
angled into middle and worked towards mid wicket where Styris surprises many by diving to save the single
back of a length and Clarke pushes back to the bowler
shorter and wider and Clarke pushes to point
slower ball attacking the stumps and Clarke works it to mid wicket where Styris moves well to prevent one
full and driven to long on
back of a length and Ponting drives on the up through cover point for four. Amazing timing and just a touch of class
good length and driven on the up back to the bowler
Tuffey really settling on his length and Clarke drives to cover
slower ball on off stump allows Clarke to work it through the leg side to rotate the strike
back to his length and Ponting pushes back to Tuffey
good length and Ponting pushes in the air towards the bowler, Tuffey dives to collect it on the bounce. Great agility from the big man
good length and Ponting pushes into the covers where Guptill dives but parries it towards mid off and they have enough time to get a single
good length again as the New Zealanders really look to settle on a length and he pushes back through mid on to the man on the fence
good length and Cl;arke works it into the leg side
straighter again and Clarke whips it through forward square leg to the man of the rope for a couple
Clarke moves forward and pushes to long on
Ponting is pushing towards mid off and steals a quick single
back of a length and Clarke pushes nicely with soft hands towards Southee at mid off again and he's weighted it pefectly to get a single
full and wide and driven majestically through the off side field to the sweeper
full slower ball driven to long on
Clarke uses his feet and hits on the up over extra cover for four, good stroke
back of a length and Clarke defends with soft hands into the off side and they take a quick single
full and driven to mid wicket off the inside half of the bat
good length and Ponting pushes back to the bowler
back of a length and wider of off stump and Clarke cuts to the off side sweeper
angled into the pads and Ponting misses out as it takes him on the thigh and falls into the leg side
good length and driven to backward point
Ponting moves back and pushes through the covers to the off side sweeper
good length and Clarke pushes into the off side and looks for a quick single but Ponting says no and Clarke is back safely
full and straight and clipped to mid wicket. The players take a well earned drinks break
straight enough for Ponting to work it through foward square leg to the leg side sweeper
attacks the stumps again and Clarke defends into the on side
short delivery and Clarke pulls through wide mid on for four past Bond who is inside the circle
Clarke uses his feet and hits over extra cover for four, good intent from Clarke
comes forward and drives to mid on, he looked for the single but hit it too well
Clarke comes down the track and Tuffey bends his back and surprises Clarke as he tries to guide it fine through third man but it takes the outside edge and through to McCullum to complete the catch
good length and driven to mid on
back of a length and pushed into the off side
fuller and Ponting is half forward and pushing into the leg side through forward square leg
back of a length and allowed through to the keeper
full and driven to cover. White just biding his time before he explodes later in the innings
bumper to finish from Oram and White hooks off the top edge fine of long leg for four
good length on off stump and Ponting defends into the off side. You won't get through that defence
slower ball driven to long on with ease. Ponting just looking to take minimal risks while he sets up the innings
good channel just outside off and White allows it through to McCullum
good length and White plays late, hitting on top of the bounce, through backward point for a couple to third man
shorter and White slashes off the back foot and it takes a thick outside edge and runs fine of third man for four
full and wide of off and White is in behind and defending into the off side
good length angling across Ponting and he pushes into the off side
full and Ponting plays too early and drives off the inside half of the bat to mid on
he waits longer for the ball to arrive this time and drives nicely to long off
good channel and defended into the leg side
good channel attacking middle stump and pushed back to the bowler
full and driven to long off. Good start from Franklin
full and angled into the pads and worked to wide mid on
full and driven back at the bowler who can't hold onto it
short and pulled through forward square leg to the leg side sweeper
shortish from Southee, Ponting looks to pull, replays show it takes a bottom edge and through to McCullum who appeals along with the bowler but local umpire Tony Hill says not out
full and driven back out Southee who does well to prevent the single even though he doesn't stop it cleanly
back of a length and driven through the off side field to the sweeper
full on middle and driven off the middle of the bat to long off
back of a length and pushed into the leg side
good length but White knows mid on is insside the circle and he drives in the air through that region for four
full and driven back past the bowler for a couple to long off
full and driven to long off
just a fraction straight and Ponting plays it nice and late, using the pace, and gets it fine of short fine leg and it races away for four
angled into the pads and whipped off his hip to deep backward square
full and driven sweetly back past the bowler for a couple as long on moves around to collect
back and driven through the off side to the sweeper
short and cut to the off side sweeper
good length and Ponting attacks, driving off the inside half of the bat to deep backward square
good length attacking off stump and White defends into the off side
back of a length on middle stump and played back to the bowler
good length and wide of off stump and Ponting throws his hands at it and it takes the inside edge and just misses the leg stump and runs away for four
fullish and driven firmly back at the bowler
good length but Ponting plays it later this time and stands tall, driving down the ground to long off
decent length on middle stump and White pushes down the gorund for a single to long off
back of a length and Ponting rolls his wrists on the ball, working it through the leg side to the sweeper
short and pulled through square leg to the sweeper
back of a length and driven back to the bowler off the back shoe
rolls his fingers across the ball and is full and White drives neatly to long on
full and straight and whipped through the leg side to the square leg boundary rider
full and angled into leg stump and White picks it up and plays through deep backward square to the man on the rope
wider of off stump and Ponting uses the pace to play to Franklin at deep point

Franklin rolls his fingers over the ball and Ponting plays too early, it takes the bat closer to the stickers than the middle and floats in the air towards cover and Guptill runs to his right, sticks his right hand out high into the air and takes a beauty. It surprised Guptill for pace and he looks pretty relieved to hold onto it. Good grab
back of a length and allowed through to McCullum
angled into middle and Hussey clips it through mid wicket to the leg side sweeper
good length attacking middle stump and pushed back to the bowler
angled down the leg side and it clips White's pad on the way through to McCullum
good length but White shows more intent and pushes to long on for a single
immediately bends his back and White pulls through mid wicket for a single to the leg side boundary rider
great channel from Bond and Hussey lets it go. That one was very close to off stump
good length and Hussey drives off the inside half of the blade to mid on

Hussey works it into mid wicket where Oram moves in from mid on to collect and he seems to place his left foot awkwardly and twists his left knee and he goes down in a real heap! He is in a lot of pain and it being carried off by his teammates. Let's hope that not the last we see of the big man. Just an awkward landing there it seems and he may well have done some ligament damage
good length and allowed through to the keeper
142 kph, back of a length and White is content on allowing it through to McCullum
draws Hussey forward into a defensive push into the off side where they sneak a quick single
full and worked to mid wicket
good length on middle stump and White pushes into the leg side and Taylor moves well from mid wicket towards the bowlers stumps to prevent the single
shapes across White and he pushes into the covers where Guptill fields safely
angled back towards the stumps and pushed back to the bowler
good length and White pushes to cover where Guptill moves quickly to his right to prevent a possible single
full and pushed back past the bowler through mid off and it runs down the slope for four. Imaculate timing
better length and defended into the off side
bumper from  Bond and it's just too short as it's called wide by the square leg umpire
searing yorker from Bond but Hussey is equal to the task and digs it out into the off side
full length and driven off the inside half of the bat to mid wicket
another yorker from Bond and Hussey drives to cover
full and wide of off stump and driven to cover
Franklin settling in nicely on middle stump and pushed to mid wicket
good channel and White pushes to mid wicket where Taylor dives full stretch to save the single
full on middle and driven powerfully back to Franklin
back of a length and White plays a fraction too early as he looks to play through the off side but he drags it back towards the bowler
around the wicket to White and all he can do is play back to the bowler. The pressure is building...
good length and White plays later this time and uses the full face to good effect, pushing to long off
147 kph, Bond goes for the yorker and it's quick. White looks to work it through mid wicket but plays it too early and gets a leading edge to mid wicket
back of a length and played into the off side
144 kph, good length and White drives nicely but straight to Guptill who shapes to throw the stumps down with his left arm. I hope he's been practising
good length and driven through point to the off side sweeper
142 kph, Bond continues to bend his back and hits a good length and Hussey defends into the on side
back of a lenth and Hussey plays it nicely, he gets close to it and lets it come, pushing to backward point for a single
half volley on middle hit straight back at the bowler
jsut outside off and guided to third man where Bond does well to prevent the boundary as he had to move a  long way
guided again to Bond at third man and he cheekily takes two when it wasn't really on, well run
back of a length and played to backward point where Broom does well to save the single
knocked into the off side, Broom charges in from point, picks it up cleanly and the throw just misses, that would've been very close
driven hard into the ground over the tall figure of Guptill at cover and long off has to move around to collect
too straight and worked through the leg side to the sweeper
angled into middle and leg and he clips it to mid wicket
White steps away to the leg side and drives through mid off
Hussey looks to use the pace and guide it fine but misses
fuller and pushed into the off side
steps away to leg again and Styris follows him nicely but he pushes down through mid on to the man on the rope
Tuffey strikes right away with the new-ish ball as he hits a good length, it seams back in just a fraction and White plays all around it. Big strike for New Zealand
good length and pushed to mid off when he calls yes then immediately no
good length and pushed into the off side
difficult length to handle from Tuffey and he guides it to third man
nicely played with soft hands to point for a quick single, the throw at the bowlers' stumps misses and Ingram is backing up but it goes through his legs and they take an overthrow
good length but Hussey is positive and pushing firmly through cover to the sweeper
rolls his fingers across this one and Hussey plays awkwardly back to the bowler
full and wide and crunched through the covers to the man on the fence
changeup from Styris and clipped to mid wicket
slower yorker from Styris and Hopes pushes into the covers
good length from Styris and Hopes uses the pace and pushes to backward point where it runs away nicely for a couple
good length and pushed into the off side. Good over from Styris
half volley outside off an Hussey drives nicely to the off side sweeper
slower ball from Tuffey and Hopes drives on the up to Guptill at cover
full and cracked straight to mid wicket. Very well timed
good length and driven towards extra cover but Guptill dives beautifully to his right to stop the single
full and wider and driven through cover to the sweeper
fuller again and driven sweetly through the off side field to the boundary rider
slower ball is short and Hussey pulls to deep backward square
back of a length at middle stump and he works it to Broom at square leg
back of a length on leg stump and worked behind square where Broom dives to restrict the scoring to one
Hussey moves back and drives through the covers
full on middle and hammered to long on, superb timing with just an economy of effort
full and whipped into mid wicket

Hussey plays into straight mid wicket, Guptill dives full stretch to save the single, Hopes has advanced down the track at the non-strikers end the throw from Guptill misses and Hopes would've been out
too straight and Hussey uses the pace and works it off his hip for a couple as Styris runs back from short fine leg
full and drvien straight to cover. That's a small victory for Tuffey, Hussey barely ever hits the fieldsman
full again and driven sweetly to long off
good length and driven on the up back past the bowler, Tuffey gets a finger to it but it runs away towards long off

full and driven towards mid off but Taylor moves quickly from cover to his left to prevent the single. New Zealand have done a good job in the field so far to keep as much pressure on the batsmen as possible
angled into leg stump and worked to mid wicket
angled down leg and clipped to backward square leg where Ingram moves quickly to pick up
Hussey improvises and laps it fine to short fine leg
full on middle and whipped to mid wicket
rolls his fingers across it and Hopes drives to cover

another slower ball and Hopes clips it in the air to Taylor at mid wicket. Taylor gets low and picks the ball up and is unsure whether or not he has caught it. They go upstairs and it looks as if it has bounced just in front of his hands
yorker length played nicely back past the bowler, Hussey looks for the second but can't get it
good length and driven on the up in the air through mid on down to long on
good length has Hussey driving uppishly back to the bowler
angled into the pads and whipped to mid wicket where Guptill runs around and fires the throw back to McCullum who takes the bails off and Hopes dives to make his ground
fullish and wide of off and Hopes plays an expansive drive but misses
good length hits Hopes dead in line with off stump but Rudi says not out and signals runs
angled down leg and Hopes clips it square of short fine leg and it runs away for four across this rapid outfield
fullish and worked into the on side
good length and played back at the bowler
full and provides just enough width for Hussey to square drive to the man on the fence at cover for a well run two
good length driven to cover
slower ball is full and driven to long off
back of a length and just enough width to guide to third man
full and wide and cracked to Guptill's right who does well to prevent a run
quicker ball from Franklin takes Hopes by surprise and hits the stickers as he tries to pull, it goes in the air and falls just short of Taylor at mid wicket
shorter and cracked through the off side field to the sweeper
half volley outside off and Hussey drives magnificently through extra cover for four, beating the off side sweeper. Glorious timing from Mr. Cricket
full and down leg this time and Hussey works it behind square on the lg side for a couple to Southee who has to move a long way and can't prevent the second
yorker dug out through mid wicket and Southee is called into action again but can't stop the second
short and cut over point to the off side sweeper Franklin, who does well to keep the scoring to one
lowe full toss driven down to Nathan McCullum at long off who is quick enough to stop the second
low full toss well wide of off stump and Hopes throws his top hand towards the ball and it hits the middle and races away through square third man for four
full again and driven firmly but straight to Guptill at cover
square driven nicely to the off side sweeper
low full toss first up and Hopes drives in the air through extra cover for a couple
yorker length but he gets underneath it and hammers it straight down the ground to long on
yorker dug out to cover
full and Hopes uses his feet and cracks it past the bowler to long off where Guptill slides nicely to pick it up but can't prevent the second
Hopes clears his front hip and tries to smash it over mid wicket but he hits the yorker length and can only ig it out to mid wicket inside the circle
Southee goes for the yorker and Hussey plays the lap and gets it over short fine leg for four, great shot and he timed the pants off it
slower ball is shortish from Bond and Hopes is beaten by the lack of pace and cue-ends the ball back to the bowler
143kph, searing yorker and Hopes can only dig it out to long on
yorker length cracked through the off side to the man on the fence
another yorker driven nicely to cover where Taylor fields well with one hand to save the second
good length and Hopes backs away to leg and cuts to the off side sweeper
yorker dug out to Taylor at extra cover and that's Hussey's fifty. Well played. A typical grafting knock with only three boundaries from Mr. Cricket
slower ball and Hussey swings it away high into the leg side and it pitches in the outfield at deep backward square and stops and they get two
slower ball yorker driven to long off, well bowled
genuine yorker from Southee and Hopes plays to cover on the 30m ring
slower length ball from Southee and Hussey swings and misses but it bounces in front of McCullum and he can't pick it up cleanly and they take a bye
Southee strikes with the yorker. If it ain't broke why fix it seems to be the mindset from Southee as Hopes tries to swing it over mid wicket but the ball cannons into middle stump
yorker length again dug out to long on to get off the mark
slower ball and Johnson doesn't pick it up early enough and he plays with softs hands back to the bowler
length ball and Johnson heaves it into the on side off the inside edge to short fine leg
low full toss and he swings it through straight mid wicket for a couple to Nathan McCullum who moves quickly around from long on
advances slightly and tries to play through the off side, it takes the inside edge and races away through the vacant fine leg for four
Bond goes full but not quite yorker length and he looks to swing it over the leg side but misses and it clips the outside of off stump and the bails trickle off the stumps
full and Hauritz uses the pace to play to short third man
low full toss and Hauritz drives powerfully back towards the bowler, Southee gets a hand to it back they get an easy single
Southee finally misses his length and Johnson gets underneath it over extra cover and it drops just over the rope, over the head of Nathan McCullum in the deep
yorker length dug out firmly back to the bowler but Southee isn't ready for it and it riccochets towards mid wicket
another yorker dug out towards mid off
low full toss and Johnson hits it as clean as a whistle over extra cover for one bounce four
slower ball and Johnson is beaten by a lack of pace as he tries to sweep it into the leg side and misses. Well disguised and good use of his variations by Southee
yorker dug out to long on. New Zealand have bowled very well at the death
low full toss whipped into the leg side to deep mid wicket where Ingram fields well
Tuffey bowls a half volley and Hauritz gets under it and chips it to long off where Nathan McCullum dives low to catch it after initially misjudging it
short and straight-pulled over long on for a one bounce four with the man at long on quite square
yorker clubbed out to deep mid wicket which allows them to grab a couple
yorker played out to deep mid wicket be he isn't able to find the gap and can only get one

inn2.comm: Harris starts well, bending his back and McCullum back cuts to third man to get underway
attacking the stumps and Ingram works it into the leg side to get away
back of a length again and McCullum guides strongly through backward point to third man

Harris attacks the stumps again and Ingram is crease bound looking to clip it through mid wicket, it takes him on the front pad and they appeal but given not out and they take a leg bye as it flies past second slip
McCullum advances and square drives through point for four. That's the same kind of intent that McCullum showed on Sunday night in Christchurch
Harris draws McCullum forward but he's beaten by some late inswing and taken high on the front pad, the appeal is loud but given not out
bumper first up from Bollinger and Ingram sees it late and ducks and it takes him on the shoulder
back of a length and Ingram drives off the back foot from the inside half of the bat into the off side
short again and wide of off stump and Ingram tries to pull from well outside off and he top edges it over the keeper for four
back of a length again from Bollinger and Ingram mistimes a back foot drive into the off side
good length again but a better line this time attacking off stump and Ingram is squared up trying to defend back down the pitch, it takes the outside edge past second slip for a single to third man
good length again just on or outside off and McCullum is tightly in behind it and defending into the off side and he looks for one but Ingram sends him back
Harris draws Ingram forward and he defends off the outside edge to second slip
back of a length and Ingram drives off the back foot to mid off
fuller angled into middle stump and Ingram works it to mid on where Johnson fields and throws at the stumps but misses and Ingram would have been out
angled down leg and McCullum works it off his hip with one hand to fine leg. McCullum looking very aggressive early on
he attacks the pads again and Ingram waits for it and times it perfectly through backward square for four
back of a length attacking middle stump and Ingram is beaten for pace and taken high on the pads
straight delivery and McCullum tries to play it fine but it takes him on the thigh and bounces back down the pitch
shortish and McCullum rocks back and pulls sweetly past Johnson at fine leg for four
shortish again and McCullum is onto it quickly and pulling through backward square for four more. Johnson dives on the boundary and gets a hand to it but can't stop it from crossing the rope
McCullum charges and leaves well outside off
half volley outside off and McCullum plays a text book cover drive for four. That's a beauty and extremely well timed
good length angled across McCullum and he tries to whip it through the leg side but misses. Interesting shot but that's what we come to expect from the dynamo
back of a length and respected from Ingram who allows it through to the keeper
good length again and Ingram is content on leaving outside off
fullish length enticing Ingram into driving on the up and he plays to mid off
full slower ball and Ingram drives to Hauritz at mid off
149 kph, back of a length angling into the pads and Ingram is beaten for pace trying to flick through the leg side, it takes his pad and flies past second slip to allow a leg bye
145 kph, McCullum charges the bowler again and attempts an ambitious drive but misses
back of a length and hit powerfully off the back foot to point where Clarke dives to field the ball
good length and Ingram pushes with soft hands into the off side
144 kph, back of a length but wider this time which allows Ingram to free the arms and swing to Clarke at point
back of a length and Ingram gets closer to this one, allows it to come and punches off the back foot through the covers for four
back of a length and Ingram plays with soft hands into the off side and sneaks a quick single, well played
good length and McCullum pushes to backward point
good channel from Harris and Ingram looks to drive off the back foot but misses
cross seam in a good channel again but Ingram punches through point off the back foot for four, he didn;t time it perfectly but this outfield is lightening quick
good length and driven back into the pitch hard and Harris gets a hand to it to stop the single
good length but gives Ingram width and he frees his arms again and hits over extra cover for four
fuller in at middle and leg and he plays to mid on who is quite close to the bat
straighter and angled w leg, Imgram tries to go inside the line and whip it into the leg side but he misses and it takes him on the thigh and trickles towards square leg
good length and McCullum moves back and defends into the off side
bumper and pulled off the top edge down fine of fine leg who dives over it and it goes for four
slower ball short delivery and he pulls but is beaten by a lack of pace and it takes him in the ribs
short outside off stump and McCullum ramps it over the cordon to third man
angled into the poads, he tries to flick it through the leg side but misses
fuller outside off and Ingram drives to mid off
slower ball just outside off and McCullum defends back down the pitch
good length and McCullum maintains his shape and drives neatly to cover
back of a length and he pushes off the back foot past the bowler to mid off
fuller this time and he swings it in the air on the bounce to Harris at mid off
driven on the up through the covers for a couple with Harris and Clarke combining in the deep
good length attacking off stump and Ingram whips it through the leg side in the air towards the sweeper but it's hit too well and races away for four
full and straight and McCullum walks across his stumps and clips it through mid wicket for a couple
full and straight again and McCullum times it sweetly to mid on
shorter delivery and McCullum mistimes the pull in the air towards Harris at fine leg
